    <description>
      <levelledPara>
        <title>General</title>
        <para>This data module contains MathML in order to produce the following:</para>
        <para>
          <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block">
            <mrow>
              <mi>x</mi>
              <mo>=</mo>
              <mfrac>
                <mrow>
                  <mo form="prefix">−</mo>
                  <mi>b</mi>
                  <mo>±</mo>
                  <msqrt>
                    <msup>
                      <mi>b</mi>
                      <mn>2</mn>
                    </msup>
                    <mo>−</mo>
                    <mn>4</mn>
                    <mo>⁢</mo>
                    <mi>a</mi>
                    <mo>⁢</mo>
                    <mi>c</mi>
                  </msqrt>
                </mrow>
                <mrow>
                  <mn>2</mn>
                  <mo>⁢</mo>
                  <mi>a</mi>
                </mrow>
              </mfrac>
            </mrow>
          </math>
        </para>
        <para>Since MathML is not supported as of S1000D Issue 4.2, this would normally fail to validate. However, the -X option allows specified XML namespaces to be ignored when validating.</para>
        <para>To ignore MathML, for example:</para>
        <para>
          <verbatimText>$ s1kd-validate -X http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML &lt;data modules&gt;</verbatimText>
        </para>
      </levelledPara>
    </description>
